        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 7:11PM EDT by NWS Tallahassee FL</headline>
        <description>At 711 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sparks, or near Nashville. The strong thunderstorm is nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Nashville, Adel, Sparks, Laconte, Cottle, and Massee.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
